# Keep `git archive` / GitHub source snapshots limited to the installable Godot addon.
#
# The Godot Asset Library installer downloads a GitHub *source archive* of this repo
# at the submitted Download Commit (not the curated release zip). Because Godot's mono
# build compiles EVERY .cs file under a project into a single assembly, any server or
# test C# left in that archive would be dropped into the consumer's project and break
# their build. The `export-ignore` directive strips everything outside the addon from
# the archive, so an Asset Library install yields only `addons/godot_mcp/` (plus the
# LICENSE and README for attribution / listing context).
#
# Scope: this affects ONLY `git archive` and the GitHub-generated source archives the
# Asset Library consumes. It does NOT touch the working tree, CI, or the `release.yml`
# `release-addon` job — that job zips `addons/godot_mcp/` directly and never calls
# `git archive`. Verify the result with: `git archive HEAD | tar -t`.
#
# See docs/RELEASING.md ("Why a .gitattributes export-ignore") for the full rationale.

/.github          export-ignore
/.gitignore       export-ignore
/.gitattributes   export-ignore
/CLAUDE.md        export-ignore
/Godot-MCP-Server export-ignore
/Godot-MCP.Tests  export-ignore
/Godot-MCP.csproj export-ignore
/Godot-MCP.sln    export-ignore
/Godot-Tests      export-ignore
/cli              export-ignore
/docs             export-ignore
